      • READ_IN_PROGRESS

        public static final int READ_IN_PROGRESS
        Transport Success: Indicates that a Channel.read(ReadArgs, Error) call on the Channel is already in progress. This can be due to another thread performing the same operation.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • READ_FD_CHANGE

        public static final int READ_FD_CHANGE
        Transport Success: Indicates that the connections channel has changed. This can occur as a result of internal connection keep-alive mechanisms. The previous channel is stored in the Channel.oldSelectableChannel() so it can be removed from the I/O notification mechanism. The Channel.selectableChannel() contains the new channel, which should be registered with the I/O notification mechanism.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • READ_PING

        public static final int READ_PING
        Transport Success: Indicates that a heartbeat message was received in Channel.read call. The ping timer should be updated.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • READ_WOULD_BLOCK

        public static final int READ_WOULD_BLOCK
        Transport Success: Reading was blocked by the OS. Typically indicates that there are no bytes available to read, returned from Channel.read.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • WRITE_CALL_AGAIN

        public static final int WRITE_CALL_AGAIN
        Transport Success: Channel.write(TransportBuffer, WriteArgs, Error) is fragmenting the buffer and needs to be called again with the same buffer. This indicates that Write was unable to send all fragments with the current call and must continue fragmenting.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • WRITE_FLUSH_FAILED

        public static final int WRITE_FLUSH_FAILED
        Transport Success: Channel.write(TransportBuffer, WriteArgs, Error) internally attempted to flush data to the connection but was blocked. This is not a failure and the user should not release their buffer.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • NO_BUFFERS

        public static final int NO_BUFFERS
        Transport Failure: There are no buffers available from the buffer pool, returned from Channel.getBuffer(int, boolean, Error). Use Channel.ioctl(int, int, Error) to increase pool size or use Channel.flush(Error) to flush data and return buffers to pool.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
